# Docker build context exclusions (issue #270, deploy S2).
#
# DELIBERATELY NOT a mirror of .gitignore. .gitignore lists `.kb/`, but the
# curated seed (`.kb/index.json`, `.kb/faiss_index/*`, `wiki/`) is force-committed
# (git add -f) as the first-run demo seed. If this file excluded `.kb/`, the image
# would ship an EMPTY index and `/chat` would fail until a key-backed rebuild.
# So `.kb/`, `wiki/`, and `docs/` are intentionally KEPT in the build context.

# Version control + local virtualenv (the image builds its own .venv).
.git
.gitignore
.venv
venv

# Python bytecode / build caches.
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info
.pytest_cache
.ruff_cache

# Eval framework telemetry + scratch.
.deepeval
.deepeval-cache.json
.tmp
.doc.local

# Eval source is excluded from the image (deepeval/matplotlib/anthropic are
# dev-only and not baked). But the Dockerfile COPYs eval's pyproject.toml
# explicitly BEFORE `COPY . .` so workspace resolution sees the manifest.
# .dockerignore filters the build context *before* any COPY runs, so the
# manifest must be re-included (negation) or that explicit COPY would fail with
# "file not found". Net effect: only the eval *source tree* is stripped, the one
# manifest survives.
eval/
!eval/paraphrase_comparison/pyproject.toml

# Test suites — not shipped in the runtime image.
**/tests/

# Local-only secrets / env (never bake credentials into an image).
.env
.env.local
.env.prod

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode
*.swp
